@clinton what do you think? seems like a suspension of immigration that's got such a short duration (30 days!; I'm sure the Trump administration will figure out whatever was "wrong" with the prior immigration system in 30 days---it couldn't possibly take longer than 30 days to ferret out purported problems in a government policy and implement effective solutions solving them; see Post blurb below for timing cite) that it's more political theater than anything, but because of the short duration, maybe harder to challenge because it'll be done with by the time it can be challenged (though it'd seem to be capable of repetition yet evading review, an exception to mootness)? I think for a suspension of immigration for so short a time, it might make more sense to use the provision Trump cited to during the campaign (which is given in the question summary) rather than the provision you've thought the administration would use, which would perhaps make more sense for a suspension of immigration that had real teeth... He may be doing it to be able to say to supporters of the campaign promise "See: I did it" rather than to have done anything of substance. Washington Post:
"Immigration experts said they had been told the orders later this week would include a halt to all admissions of refugees for 120 days, including from the Syrian civil war, and a 30-day pause in the issuance of immigrant and non-immigrant visas to people from some predominantly Muslim countries."
